# AkwaabaFit AI — Installation guide (from zero)

This guide assumes you have **never deployed this project before**. It walks through:

1. **Windows PC** — run the API locally while building the Flutter app  
2. **HP ProBook (Ubuntu)** — production API with **Cloudflare** (HTTPS for mobile + Paystack)  
3. **Mobile app** — point Flutter at your API URL  

The repo has three folders:

| Folder | What it is | Runs on server? |
|--------|------------|-----------------|
| **`Backend/`** | Laravel API, admin web, Paystack webhooks | **Yes** (ProBook) |
| **`Mobile/`** | Flutter app (Android / iOS) | No — build on your PC |
| **`AI/`** | YOLO training scripts (optional) | No — only if retraining the food model |

**Food scanning** uses an **ONNX model bundled in the mobile app**. You do **not** need Python on the ProBook for normal operation.

---

## 0. What you are building (picture)

```text
[ Flutter app on phone ]
        │  HTTPS JSON  /api/*
        ▼
[ Cloudflare ] ──► [ Cloudflare Tunnel on ProBook ]
                          │
                          ▼
                   [ Apache :80 ]
                          │
                          ▼
              [ Laravel Backend/public ]
                          │
                          ▼
                   [ MariaDB: akwaabafit ]
```

Paystack sends webhooks to the same public HTTPS host:

```text
https://api.YOUR-DOMAIN.com/api/webhook/paystack
```

If the **same ProBook** also runs **TesNet** (`192.168.88.2`), that is fine — different folder, different database, different domain. See [§12 Running alongside TesNet](#12-running-alongside-tesnet-on-the-same-probook).

