## 2. Part A — Windows PC (local development)

Use this path on your PC:

```text
C:\Apache24\htdocs\AkwaabaFitAIProject
```

### 2.1 Install tools (one-time)

| Tool | Version | Download |
|------|---------|----------|
| **PHP** | 8.3+ | [windows.php.net](https://windows.php.net/) or XAMPP/Apache stack |
| **Composer** | latest | [getcomposer.org](https://getcomposer.org) |
| **Node.js** | 18+ | [nodejs.org](https://nodejs.org) |
| **MySQL / MariaDB** | 8+ | XAMPP, WAMP, or standalone |
| **Flutter** | 3.10+ | [flutter.dev](https://flutter.dev) — run `flutter doctor` |

Enable PHP extensions: `pdo_mysql`, `mbstring`, `openssl`, `tokenizer`, `xml`, `ctype`, `json`, `fileinfo`.

### 2.2 Create the database (Windows)

Open MySQL (phpMyAdmin or CLI):

```sql
CREATE DATABASE akwaabafit CHARACTER SET utf8mb4 COLLATE utf8mb4_unicode_ci;
```

### 2.3 Backend setup (Windows)

Open **PowerShell**:

```powershell
cd C:\Apache24\htdocs\AkwaabaFitAIProject\Backend

composer install
npm install
copy .env.example .env
php artisan key:generate
```

Edit **`Backend\.env`** (minimum for local):

```env
APP_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8000

DB_DATABASE=akwaabafit
DB_USERNAME=root
DB_PASSWORD=YOUR_MYSQL_PASSWORD

QUEUE_CONNECTION=database
```

Run migrations and seed food data:

```powershell
php artisan migrate
php artisan db:seed
php artisan storage:link
npm run build
```

Start the API:

```powershell
php artisan serve
```

API base URL for local tools: `http://127.0.0.1:8000/api`

Optional — queue worker (push notifications / jobs):

```powershell
php artisan queue:work
```

**Quick test:**

```powershell
php artisan test
curl http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/app/version?platform=android^&version=1.0.0
```

### 2.4 Mobile app (Windows → phone/emulator)

```powershell
cd C:\Apache24\htdocs\AkwaabaFitAIProject\Mobile
flutter pub get
```

| Device | `API_BASE_URL` |
|--------|----------------|
| Android emulator | `http://10.0.2.2:8000/api` |
| Physical phone (same Wi‑Fi as PC) | `http://YOUR-PC-LAN-IP:8000/api` |
| ngrok (Paystack test from phone) | `https://xxxx.ngrok-free.app/api` |

Run:

```powershell
flutter run --dart-define=API_BASE_URL=http://10.0.2.2:8000/api
```

**Firebase:** copy `google-services.json` (Android) and `GoogleService-Info.plist` (iOS) from your Firebase console into the Mobile project. Without them, the app runs but **push notifications fail**.

### 2.5 Paystack on Windows (testing)

1. Start ngrok: `ngrok http 8000`
2. Set `APP_URL=https://YOUR-SUBDOMAIN.ngrok-free.app` in `.env`
3. Paystack dashboard → Webhook URL:

   ```text
   https://YOUR-SUBDOMAIN.ngrok-free.app/api/webhook/paystack
   ```

4. Restart `php artisan serve` after `.env` changes.

