## 3. Part B — ProBook (Ubuntu Server) — first-time OS setup

Skip this section if Ubuntu is **already installed** and you only need the app (go to §4).

### 3.1 Install Ubuntu Server

1. Download **Ubuntu Server 24.04 LTS** from [ubuntu.com/download/server](https://ubuntu.com/download/server).
2. Boot ProBook from USB → install with **OpenSSH** enabled.
3. Hostname example: `akwaabafit-server`
4. User example: `tesnet` (same user as TesNet is OK)

```bash
sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y
sudo reboot
```

### 3.2 Static IP (if ProBook is on TesNet LAN)

If the ProBook sits on the MikroTik LAN at `192.168.88.2`, you already have Netplan from TesNet — **do not change it** unless you know what you are doing.

Check connectivity:

```bash
ip a
ping -c 3 8.8.8.8
```

### 3.3 Install software (ProBook)

```bash
sudo apt install -y software-properties-common curl git unzip \
  apache2 mariadb-server mariadb-client \
  php8.3 php8.3-cli php8.3-fpm php8.3-mysql php8.3-xml php8.3-mbstring \
  php8.3-curl php8.3-zip php8.3-bcmath php8.3-intl libapache2-mod-php8.3
```

**Composer:**

```bash
curl -sS https://getcomposer.org/installer | php
sudo mv composer.phar /usr/local/bin/composer
composer --version
```

**Node.js 20** (Vite assets):

```bash
curl -fsSL https://deb.nodesource.com/setup_20.x | sudo -E bash -
sudo apt install -y nodejs
node --version
```

**Apache:**

```bash
sudo a2enmod rewrite headers
sudo systemctl enable --now apache2 mariadb
```

### 3.4 Firewall (UFW)

If TesNet already configured UFW, you mainly need **outbound** internet for Cloudflare Tunnel. Optional:

```bash
sudo ufw allow OpenSSH
sudo ufw allow from 192.168.88.0/24 to any port 80,443 proto tcp
sudo ufw enable
```

Cloudflare Tunnel does **not** require opening inbound port 443 from the internet.

