## 4. Part C — MariaDB on ProBook

Use a **separate database** from TesNet (`tesnet`).

```bash
sudo mysql_secure_installation
sudo mysql
```

```sql
CREATE DATABASE akwaabafit CHARACTER SET utf8mb4 COLLATE utf8mb4_unicode_ci;
CREATE USER 'akwaabafit'@'localhost' IDENTIFIED BY 'STRONG_DB_PASSWORD_HERE';
GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON akwaabafit.* TO 'akwaabafit'@'localhost';
FLUSH PRIVILEGES;
EXIT;
```

Save the password — you will paste it into `.env`.

