## 6. Part E — Apache virtual host

This site runs **alongside TesNet** on the same Apache — a **second** config file.

```bash
sudo nano /etc/apache2/sites-available/akwaabafit.conf
```

```apache
<VirtualHost *:80>
    ServerName api.YOUR-DOMAIN.com
    DocumentRoot /var/www/AkwaabaFitAIProject/Backend/public

    <Directory /var/www/AkwaabaFitAIProject/Backend/public>
        AllowOverride All
        Require all granted
    </Directory>

    ErrorLog ${APACHE_LOG_DIR}/akwaabafit-error.log
    CustomLog ${APACHE_LOG_DIR}/akwaabafit-access.log combined
</VirtualHost>
```

Enable:

```bash
sudo a2ensite akwaabafit.conf
sudo systemctl reload apache2
```

Test locally (before Cloudflare):

```bash
curl -sI -H "Host: api.YOUR-DOMAIN.com" http://127.0.0.1/ | head -5
```

**Leave TesNet’s `tesnet.conf` unchanged** (`ServerName 192.168.88.2`).

