## 8. Part G — Queue worker and scheduler

The app uses **database queues** for push notifications and background jobs.

### 8.1 Systemd queue service

```bash
sudo nano /etc/systemd/system/akwaabafit-queue.service
```

```ini
[Unit]
Description=AkwaabaFit queue worker
After=network.target mariadb.service

[Service]
User=www-data
Group=www-data
Restart=always
RestartSec=5
WorkingDirectory=/var/www/AkwaabaFitAIProject/Backend
ExecStart=/usr/bin/php artisan queue:work --sleep=3 --tries=3 --max-time=3600

[Install]
WantedBy=multi-user.target
```

```bash
sudo systemctl daemon-reload
sudo systemctl enable --now akwaabafit-queue
sudo systemctl status akwaabafit-queue
```

### 8.2 Cron (Laravel scheduler)

```bash
sudo crontab -u www-data -e
```

Add (keep any existing TesNet lines):

```cron
* * * * * cd /var/www/AkwaabaFitAIProject/Backend && php artisan schedule:run >> /dev/null 2>&1
```

### 8.3 Optional — Reverb WebSockets

Mobile chat uses **HTTP polling** today; Reverb is optional.

```bash
sudo nano /etc/systemd/system/akwaabafit-reverb.service
```

```ini
[Unit]
Description=AkwaabaFit Reverb WebSocket server
After=network.target

[Service]
User=www-data
Group=www-data
Restart=always
WorkingDirectory=/var/www/AkwaabaFitAIProject/Backend
ExecStart=/usr/bin/php artisan reverb:start --host=127.0.0.1 --port=8080

[Install]
WantedBy=multi-user.target
```

Only enable if you configure clients to use Reverb.

